    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "\"pick up the pieces\"... i wish it was that simple. it doesn't feel like picking up pieces, it feels like being buried under them. everybody thinks i'm this visionary, this success story. the shame is crushing. i can't even look my wife in the eye because i know she's looking at the person who lost everything we built. there's no \"starting over\" when you've lost your dignity. how do you even live with that weight?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Dignity is a mask that's torn off, and beneath, the weight of vulnerability is excruciating. You're right, there's no going back, but if you can't look at yourself, how can you begin to heal? Lean on the pain, process it, and slowly the ground beneath will shift, allowing you to find your feet and face the person staring back at you with a glimmer of hope.",
      "source": "target",
